<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="x_gal">X-Gal</a> - A colourless <a href="#galactose">galactose</a> <a href="#derivative">derivative</a>. When <a href="#cleavage">cleaved</a> by <a href="#β_galactosidase_lactase_β_gal_beta_gal">β-galactosidase</a> (encoded by the <a href="#lacz">LacZ gene</a>), gives rise to two products: <a href="#galactose">galactose</a> and an <a href="#indole">indole</a>. <a href="#indole">Indole</a> spontaneously forms a <a href="#dimer">dimer</a> which has a blue colour. This allows to test for the presence of <a href="#β_galactosidase_lactase_β_gal_beta_gal">β-galactosidase</a> activity and by extension the activity or presence of the <a href="#lacz">LacZ gene</a>.